g critical tendencies that read mid-century poetry in terms of expressive modes of individualism, Poetic Community demonstrates that the most important literary innovations of the post-war period were the results of intensive collaboration and social action opposing the Cold War’s ideological enclosures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCold WarxInfluence. 0aLiterary movementsxHistoryy20th century. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy20th century. 0aPoetryxSocial aspects. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266215540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442662155423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442662155.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK